author: cbs8
title: Jefferson Sheriff's Office: Vitter unhurt in car accident
text:
METAIRIE, La. (AP) - Jefferson Parish authorities say U.S. Sen. David Vitter was unharmed in a Metairie traffic accident.
The Jefferson Parish Sheriff's Office says Vitter was a passenger in a Mercedes Benz that struck a Honda Civic on Friday afternoon. The woman driving the Mercedes in which Vitter was riding was ticketed for improper lane usage.
A woman driving the Honda complained of hand pain but refused medical attention. No other injuries were reported.
